<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="139" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
Clypeus reddish brown; palpus pale yellow; gonopods roundly expanded in lateral view. (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. Scaptodrosophila riverata (Singh &amp; Gupta, 1977) ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B surstylus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view) E oviscapt (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416842" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">7C, D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="139" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
(♂, ♀) 
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Head</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Head, mesonotum, scutellum, pleura and abdomen of male. A, C, E S. riverata (Singh &amp; Gupta, 1977) B, D, F S. puncticeps (Okada, 1956). Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416838" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">3B</figureCitation>
): Frons reddish brown. Pedicel yellowish brown. Facial carina creamy white, short, 1/3 length as face.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Thorax</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Head, mesonotum, scutellum, pleura and abdomen of male. A, C, E S. riverata (Singh &amp; Gupta, 1977) B, D, F S. puncticeps (Okada, 1956). Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416838" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">3D, F</figureCitation>
): Mesonotum and scutellum yellow. Acrostichal setulae in ca 7 irregular rows. Halter yellowish brown. Wing greyish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Abdomen</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Head, mesonotum, scutellum, pleura and abdomen of male. A, C, E S. riverata (Singh &amp; Gupta, 1977) B, D, F S. puncticeps (Okada, 1956). Scale bars: 0.5 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416838" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">3D, F</figureCitation>
): Tergites yellowish brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Male terminalia</emphasis>
: Epandrium with ca 21 setae near posterior margin and ventral corner on each side (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Scaptodrosophila puncticeps (Okada, 1956) ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view) E oviscapt (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416843" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">8A, B</figureCitation>
). Surstylus small with 10 peg-like prensisetae on caudal margin, and ca 16 setae on outer and inner surface (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Scaptodrosophila puncticeps (Okada, 1956) ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view) E oviscapt (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416843" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">8A, B</figureCitation>
). Hypandrium pubescent near paramedian setae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Scaptodrosophila puncticeps (Okada, 1956) ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view) E oviscapt (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416843" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">8C, D</figureCitation>
). Paramere broadened medially with ca 3 sensilla (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Scaptodrosophila puncticeps (Okada, 1956) ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view) E oviscapt (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416843" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">8C, D</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus broadened apically, curved medially, sickle-shaped anteriorly in lateral view (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Scaptodrosophila puncticeps (Okada, 1956) ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view) E oviscapt (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416843" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">8C, D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="139">
<emphasis bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">Female terminalia</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F8" captionText="Figure 8. Scaptodrosophila puncticeps (Okada, 1956) ♂. A Epandrium, surstylus and cercus (posterior view) B epandrium, surstylus and cercus (lateral view) C hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (ventral view) D hypandrium, aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme, paramere and gonopods (lateral view) E oviscapt (lateral view). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.937.49794.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/416843" pageId="0" pageNumber="139">8E</figureCitation>
): Oviscapt densely covered with peg-like ovisensilla.
</paragraph>
